mplayer: MPlayer and MEncoder (video player/encoder)
mplayer:
mplayer: MPlayer is a movie player for Linux (runs on many other Unices,
mplayer: and non-x86 CPUs, see the documentation). It plays most MPEG, VOB,
mplayer: AVI, Ogg/OGM, VIVO, ASF/WMA/WMV, QT/MOV/MP4, FLI, RM, NuppelVideo,
mplayer: YUV4MPEG, FILM, RoQ, PVA files, supported by many native, XAnim,
mplayer: and Win32 DLL codecs. You can watch VideoCD, SVCD, DVD, 3ivx,
mplayer: DivX 3/4/5 and even WMV movies, too (without the avifile library).
mplayer:
